Templates.template:
new sap.zen.crosstab.Crosstab(
	"${sId}", // string
	{
		id: ${id}, // sap.ui.core.ID
		models: ${models}, // object
		bindingContexts: ${bindingContexts}, // object
		objectBindings: ${objectBindings}, // object
		metadataContexts: ${metadataContexts}, // object
		validationSuccess: [function (oEvent) {}, this], // function|array
		validationError: [function (oEvent) {}, this], // function|array
		parseError: [function (oEvent) {}, this], // function|array
		formatError: [function (oEvent) {}, this], // function|array
		modelContextChange: [function (oEvent) {}, this], // function|array
		tooltip: ${tooltip}, // sap.ui.core.TooltipBase
		customData: [${customData}], // sap.ui.core.CustomData[]
		layoutData: ${layoutData}, // sap.ui.core.LayoutData
		dependents: [${dependents}], // sap.ui.core.Element[]
		dragDropConfig: [${dragDropConfig}], // sap.ui.core.dnd.DragDropBase[]
		fieldHelpDisplay: ${fieldHelpDisplay}, // (sap.ui.core.Element|string)
		blocked: ${bBlocked}, // boolean
		busy: ${bBusy}, // boolean
		busyIndicatorDelay: ${1000}, // int
		busyIndicatorSize: ${sap.ui.core.BusyIndicatorSize.Medium}, // sap.ui.core.BusyIndicatorSize
		visible: ${bVisible}, // boolean
		fieldGroupIds: [${fieldGroupIds}], // string[]
		validateFieldGroup: [function (oEvent) {}, this], // function|array
		width: ${width}, // sap.ui.core.CSSSize
		height: ${height} // sap.ui.core.CSSSize
	}
)
Templates.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new Crosstab. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getWidth width} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize
    • {@link #getHeight height} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

Templates.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new HeaderCell. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getRowSpan rowSpan} : int
    • {@link #getColSpan colSpan} : int
    • {@link #getText text} : string
    • {@link #getFormatter formatter} : object
    • {@link #getMergeKey mergeKey} : string
    • {@link #getSort sort} : string
    • {@link #getSortAction sortAction} : string
    • {@link #getArea area} : object
    • {@link #getEffectiveColSpan effectiveColSpan} : int
    • {@link #getEffectiveRowSpan effectiveRowSpan} : int
    • {@link #getRow row} : int
    • {@link #getCol col} : int
    • {@link #getLevel level} : int
    • {@link #getDrillState drillState} : string
    • {@link #getHierarchyAction hierarchyAction} : string
    • {@link #getHierarchyTooltip hierarchyTooltip} : string
    • {@link #getHtmlIE8RowSpan htmlIE8RowSpan} : int (default: 1)
    • {@link #getSortTextIndex sortTextIndex} : int
    • {@link #getTableRow tableRow} : int
    • {@link #getTableCol tableCol} : int
    • {@link #getAlignment alignment} : string
    • {@link #getMemberId memberId} : string
    • {@link #getParentMemberId parentMemberId} : string
    • {@link #getNodeAlignment nodeAlignment} : string
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.
